17:40.477 --> 17:42.104
Sounds pricey.

17:42.104 --> 17:46.358
‐ RMV has plenty of empty stages.
We just need a phone line.

17:49.736 --> 17:54.074
Uh, and it all culminates into

17:54.074 --> 17:56.869
a daily live countdown show.

17:59.037 --> 18:00.664
‐ Do me a write‐up.

18:01.415 --> 18:04.168
A treatment, some sample scripts,

18:04.168 --> 18:07.713
budget, list of guests that could come on.

18:11.884 --> 18:13.635
How did you know I'd ask for this?

18:14.636 --> 18:15.971
‐ I didn't.

18:19.099 --> 18:21.185
‐ Obviously, I don't need an assistant.

18:23.020 --> 18:26.023
Perhaps an associate producer.

18:26.023 --> 18:28.859
♪ instrumental music ♪

18:28.859 --> 18:33.030
♪

18:35.282 --> 18:38.368
Uh, Anna, who‐‐ who does your hair?

18:39.536 --> 18:40.704
‐ No one.

18:41.246 --> 18:42.331
Me.

18:43.707 --> 18:45.334
‐ Aren't you tired of it?

18:46.543 --> 18:49.463
All the stares you get
walking through the RMV lobby?

18:49.463 --> 18:51.590
Everyone wondering why you're here.

18:52.257 --> 18:56.762
If you went to any other floor
in this tower for a job interview,

18:56.762 --> 18:58.597
you wouldn't get past reception.

18:59.515 --> 19:00.891
And you know that.

19:02.184 --> 19:04.895
Sistas get fired for less than that
every day.

19:06.021 --> 19:10.108
Now, music people have
certain expectations,

19:10.108 --> 19:12.819
and my girls need to flow freely.

19:14.863 --> 19:17.950
I wonder, do you want to be
one of my girls?

19:17.950 --> 19:18.867
‐ Yes.

19:23.247 --> 19:25.832
♪ ominous music playing ♪

19:25.832 --> 19:28.877
♪

19:49.106 --> 19:50.315
AMOS:
Anna's living in a fantasy.

19:50.315 --> 19:51.984
I mean, how long‐‐
[throat clears]

19:51.984 --> 19:54.695
Uh, so this is the book Mama gave me‐‐
MAXINE: Hey, baby.

19:54.695 --> 19:57.865
‐ Uh, took me years to track it down.

19:57.865 --> 20:01.785
‐ Look who decided to grace us
with her presence.

20:01.785 --> 20:02.744
‐ Unc.

20:02.744 --> 20:04.746
AMOS:
Mama used to know all these by heart.

20:04.746 --> 20:06.999
Almost wondered if there was even
an actual book.

20:06.999 --> 20:08.876
‐ Something new for his
wall of oppression.

20:08.876 --> 20:10.627
‐ Child, please.
[laughing]

20:10.627 --> 20:13.714
[all chattering]
KIEREN: Does it have the, um...
what was it?

20:13.714 --> 20:17.885
"Skinny, Skinny" story.
AMOS: "Skinny, skinny, don't you know me."

20:17.885 --> 20:19.094
[laughs]

20:19.094 --> 20:21.763
‐ It's a folk tale the slaves
used to tell about witches

20:21.763 --> 20:24.057
who would leave their own skin
at night to go haunting.

20:24.057 --> 20:26.059
‐ Oh. [chuckles]
AMOS: Aah.

20:26.059 --> 20:29.354
"Moss Hair Girl."
That was the one Mom used to tell.

20:29.354 --> 20:31.356
‐ Uh, can I take a look?

20:32.566 --> 20:34.943
‐ Uh, yeah.
‐ Thank you.

20:34.943 --> 20:37.404
‐ So, Anna, how's work?

20:37.404 --> 20:39.823
‐ Intense.
LINDA: Um, I can relate to that.

20:39.823 --> 20:41.742
‐ I hardly see this one anymore.

20:41.742 --> 20:45.871
‐ Well, they have me teaching history now,
in addition to English lit,

20:45.871 --> 20:48.916
and I just started an after school
college prep program.

20:48.916 --> 20:50.751
AMOS: Remarkable.
‐ Uh‐‐

20:50.751 --> 20:53.754
I'm sorry. Anna, I cut you off.
You were talking about work?

20:53.754 --> 20:55.339
‐ Now, are you still interning
for that lady?

20:55.339 --> 20:59.426
‐ Executive assistant, and no.

20:59.426 --> 21:01.094
Actually, she left the company.

21:01.094 --> 21:03.847
‐ Oh. Your job's not
in jeopardy now, is it?

21:03.847 --> 21:06.141
ANNA:
No! Not at all.

21:06.141 --> 21:07.643
Look, they're doing some retooling,

21:07.643 --> 21:11.271
and actually, they're looking at giving me
my own show, so...

21:11.271 --> 21:13.023
‐ When does it air, Anna?

21:15.442 --> 21:18.320
‐ I mean, there's still a lot to do,
so it might be a while,

21:18.320 --> 21:20.364
but it's all moving along.

21:20.364 --> 21:22.032
‐ Hope it works out.

21:22.032 --> 21:24.618
ANNA: It already is, so...
[Kieren laughs]

21:24.618 --> 21:27.496
‐ Oh, the flying African story.
I did my thesis on these.

21:27.496 --> 21:29.748
AMOS: Yes!
LINDA: No, that's in there?

21:29.748 --> 21:31.333
‐ It's ridiculous.

21:31.333 --> 21:32.417
AMOS: I'm sorry?

21:35.462 --> 21:37.339
‐ I'm just, um,

21:37.339 --> 21:40.926
surprised to see a room
full of people

21:40.926 --> 21:42.928
with doctorates, like,

21:42.928 --> 21:45.973
trippin' over superstitions
and fairy tales.

21:45.973 --> 21:47.224
‐ Fairy tales.

21:48.350 --> 21:50.102
Humph. [laughs]

21:50.102 --> 21:52.229
How does one group of people
subjugate another?

21:52.229 --> 21:54.606
MAXINE: Uh, Amos...
AMOS: No, no, no.
I'm just educating the girl.

21:55.440 --> 21:57.359
You subjugate a people

21:57.359 --> 22:00.696
by telling them their science
is superstition,

22:00.696 --> 22:04.575
their faith is heresy,
and their wisdom is make‐believe.

22:04.575 --> 22:06.869
They called the American Indians savages.

22:06.869 --> 22:08.120
And they called us...

22:09.288 --> 22:10.497
Well, what didn't they call us?

22:10.497 --> 22:13.458
‐ I got it, okay?
‐ No, you don't get it.

22:13.458 --> 22:16.670
From the moment you are born,
you are so thoroughly indoctrinated

22:16.670 --> 22:19.464
by the insanity of
Western European world views,

22:19.464 --> 22:23.468
you can't bear to see yourself
the way nature would have.

22:23.468 --> 22:27.556
And you scoff at us and our superstitions.
Well...

22:27.556 --> 22:31.643
those superstitions are in fact
tributaries leading to rivers

22:31.643 --> 22:35.647
and oceans of truth
about what you really are.

22:35.647 --> 22:37.941
And who you might have been.

22:37.941 --> 22:41.320
♪

22:41.320 --> 22:42.821
Someone pass the salt.

22:43.614 --> 22:47.075
MAXINE:
Uh, why you never bring Julius?

22:47.075 --> 22:49.536
ANNA:
His show is doing really well, so...

22:49.536 --> 22:50.829
it keeps him busy.

22:50.829 --> 22:53.248
‐ Hmm.
‐ Our show, really.

22:53.248 --> 22:55.250
‐ But you're making your rent, right?

22:56.126 --> 22:58.045
Anna, no. Your credit.

22:58.045 --> 23:00.297
You can't mess with that. Baby‐‐
‐ They wanna raise the rent 500‐‐

23:00.297 --> 23:02.758
‐ What? What? 500?

23:02.758 --> 23:04.718
‐ Five hundred bucks. I'll figure it out.

23:04.718 --> 23:06.637
‐ No, that is outrageous.

23:06.637 --> 23:09.223
‐ White folks started moving in, so...

23:09.223 --> 23:12.684
‐ Well, they have a habit
of doing that, don't they?

23:13.477 --> 23:15.103
ANNA: Auntie, no.
MAXINE: Mm‐mm.

23:15.103 --> 23:18.941
Please. Your uncle doesn't know anything
about my little account.

23:18.941 --> 23:24.029
Humph. Besides, you can pay me back
when your show comes through.

23:24.446 --> 23:25.656
Okay?

23:28.951 --> 23:29.826
Okay.

23:30.911 --> 23:32.579
Mm. So...

23:32.579 --> 23:34.164
We finally gonna do something‐‐
‐ Auntie!

23:34.164 --> 23:37.376
‐ Oh, okay. All right. I'm just sayin'...

23:37.376 --> 23:40.170
Wigs have gone a long way since,
you know...

23:40.170 --> 23:41.839
last time you tried 'em.

23:41.839 --> 23:43.757
ANNA: What'd you want me to do with that?

23:44.341 --> 23:45.968
AMOS: It's a book. People read 'em.

23:47.135 --> 23:48.428
‐ I'm good.

23:51.265 --> 23:54.518
‐ I forget to leave Professor Bludso
at work sometimes.

23:55.686 --> 23:56.895
I'm sorry.

23:59.231 --> 24:02.025
‐ Don't you think Kieren might be
more into that folklore stuff?

24:02.025 --> 24:03.527
‐ You're into it, too.

24:03.527 --> 24:06.864
As long as it involves a fly girl
making it big in the city.

24:06.864 --> 24:09.199
[Annie chuckles]
Starring Sandra. [laughs]

24:09.199 --> 24:11.034
‐ A fly girl, huh?
‐ Hey.

24:11.034 --> 24:14.621
♪

24:14.621 --> 24:16.790
Their stories run the world.

24:16.790 --> 24:19.334
Sure as the sun, these are ours.

24:26.008 --> 24:28.135
♪ singing and humming "I Get It" ♪

24:43.650 --> 24:45.986
♪ "I Get It" playing on radio ♪

24:50.908 --> 24:51.867
‐ Hi.

24:51.867 --> 24:55.037
ANNA:
Um, are your prices listed?

24:55.037 --> 24:56.622
‐ Oh, for a sew in?

24:56.622 --> 24:59.625
‐ Yeah.
‐ Oh, hair and service is 450.

25:00.876 --> 25:02.920
‐ Four hundred and fifty?
‐ Mm.

25:02.920 --> 25:05.964
And Virgie's earliest appointment
is the 15th...

25:05.964 --> 25:07.466
of February.

25:07.925 --> 25:10.844
‐ Look, sista to sista,

25:10.844 --> 25:12.429
I work in TV.

25:12.429 --> 25:14.348
I'm actually a VJ at Culture,

25:14.348 --> 25:18.018
and girl to girl, I really need this.

25:18.018 --> 25:21.230
‐ Well, I can see that.

25:21.230 --> 25:25.859
Look, I don't know how it works
in your hood, or wherever.

25:25.859 --> 25:30.322
But we are a world‐class salon, okay?

25:30.322 --> 25:34.159
Look, I'm sure you can find
someone else to hook you up.

25:37.663 --> 25:39.039
‐ ♪ I get it ♪

25:39.039 --> 25:40.332
‐ Excuse me!

25:41.708 --> 25:43.502
‐ Hi.
‐ Uh, Denise?

25:43.502 --> 25:45.212
ANNA: Please. I just need a moment.

25:45.212 --> 25:47.297
You ever had a dream?

25:47.297 --> 25:49.466
One you'd be willing
to do anything for?

25:49.466 --> 25:52.261
‐ Very few things are worth
doing anything for, baby.

25:52.261 --> 25:55.597
‐ Right. Especially when
everyone says you can't do it.

25:55.597 --> 25:57.266
You don't deserve this,
says you don't belong

25:57.266 --> 25:59.685
where you know
your destiny tells you to be.

26:00.185 --> 26:02.271
Sista, have you ever been there?

26:03.105 --> 26:04.481
VIRGIE:
Okay.

26:04.481 --> 26:06.608
It'll be my good deed for the day.

26:07.818 --> 26:11.697
[laughs]
‐ You can wait over there
until she can slip you in.

26:12.698 --> 26:15.117
♪ "Break U" playing on TV ♪

26:16.618 --> 26:19.955
‐ ♪ Don't wanna break you, break you ♪

26:19.955 --> 26:23.625
♪ We just can't do the things
that lovers do ♪

26:23.625 --> 26:26.420
♪ I gotta break you, break you ♪

26:26.420 --> 26:28.380
♪ mysterious music playing ♪

26:28.380 --> 26:32.801
♪

27:01.914 --> 27:03.540
VIRGIE:
Sweetheart.

27:08.170 --> 27:09.796
All right, baby.

27:10.756 --> 27:12.257
Let's find her.

27:14.885 --> 27:17.012
Go on and look around, honey.

27:18.555 --> 27:21.308
You won't see my supply
at any other salon.

27:25.395 --> 27:27.272
My sources are exclusive.

27:29.316 --> 27:31.485
[Anna laughing]

27:35.614 --> 27:38.116
[voices whispering]

27:39.535 --> 27:40.953
I thought so.

27:42.454 --> 27:44.748
‐ I really do feel something.

27:44.748 --> 27:46.750
VIRGIE:
Clients wear this stuff as magic.

27:48.418 --> 27:50.295
You know, in some parts of India,

27:50.295 --> 27:53.423
a woman's hair is her
most prized possession.

27:53.423 --> 27:56.635
It's the greatest sacrifice
she can make to her gods. [laughs]

27:56.635 --> 27:58.929
‐ This came all the way from India?

27:58.929 --> 28:00.848
‐ Forget about where it's from.

28:02.182 --> 28:04.059
Let's focus on where it's going.

28:04.059 --> 28:06.728
[both laughing]

28:10.524 --> 28:12.818
You're not tender‐headed, are you?

28:12.818 --> 28:13.986
[Annie screaming]
LINDA: I'm sorry!

28:13.986 --> 28:15.571
‐ I'll be fine.

28:21.493 --> 28:22.828
[whimpers]

28:27.374 --> 28:28.375
[whimpers]

28:29.751 --> 28:32.171
♪ ominous music playing ♪

28:32.171 --> 28:36.800
♪

28:43.182 --> 28:44.516
[moaning]

28:56.403 --> 28:57.696
Aah.

29:01.909 --> 29:03.202
[shuddering]:
Ow.

29:04.244 --> 29:05.287
[pained moan]

29:10.292 --> 29:11.960
[panting, crying]

29:14.588 --> 29:17.174
‐ My mama used a hot comb on me.

29:17.174 --> 29:18.842
[pained laughter]

29:18.842 --> 29:21.553
And she burned the shit
out of my scalp.

29:23.514 --> 29:24.806
[pained gasping]

29:30.020 --> 29:31.939
‐ Ow. Ow.

29:31.939 --> 29:33.690
[pained moaning]

29:36.693 --> 29:37.986
You almost finished?

29:52.668 --> 29:53.710
Ow.

29:56.922 --> 29:57.923
[pained wince]

30:00.759 --> 30:01.718
[whimpers]

30:05.806 --> 30:06.849
[squishing]

30:07.224 --> 30:09.601
♪ ominous music playing ♪

30:10.853 --> 30:13.063
[Anna grunts]

30:14.022 --> 30:15.274
VIRGIE:
Sweetheart.

30:15.274 --> 30:19.152
‐ I'm sorry, I‐‐ I've never had
my hair done before.

30:21.238 --> 30:22.531
[screams]

30:22.531 --> 30:23.365
[shatters]

30:23.365 --> 30:24.700
[whimpers]

30:31.707 --> 30:32.875
[gasps]

30:36.295 --> 30:38.255
‐ You're not the first to faint.

30:38.255 --> 30:39.298
[moans]

30:40.632 --> 30:41.758
‐ Ow.

30:42.926 --> 30:44.136
[moans]

31:03.363 --> 31:05.657
It's...
VIRGIE: Stunning.

31:12.539 --> 31:15.083
My line of essential oils for the scalp.

31:15.709 --> 31:17.336
Proprietary blend.

31:18.045 --> 31:21.423
You want to get it between your braids
and work it into the hair,

31:21.423 --> 31:23.175
at least twice a day.

31:23.175 --> 31:26.011
Trust me. And never get it wet.

31:27.054 --> 31:29.181
It'll hurt for the first week or so.

31:29.181 --> 31:32.518
A lot, but that's normal
for the first time.

31:33.810 --> 31:35.479
But once you get through it,

31:37.022 --> 31:39.775
I'll never be this bad again, okay?
[bell on door jingles]

31:40.776 --> 31:43.946
WOMAN: I thought you said
there wouldn't be anybody else here.

31:43.946 --> 31:45.572
VIRGIE:
She's leaving.

31:47.616 --> 31:50.702
‐ When she tells you not to get it wet,
believe her.

31:51.411 --> 31:53.038
VIRGIE:
What the hell, Sandra?

31:53.038 --> 31:54.414
‐ Rain at the venue.

31:54.998 --> 31:57.835
Manager wanted a Diana Ross moment.

31:57.835 --> 31:59.461
‐ Oh, such a fan.

31:59.461 --> 32:03.257
I work for Culture, and it's all because
growing up, I saw you.

32:03.257 --> 32:05.008
Someone who looks like me on TV.

32:05.926 --> 32:08.554
Love, love the new video.

32:09.471 --> 32:11.014
‐ So does the label.

32:11.598 --> 32:12.683
♪ "I Get It" playing on TV ♪

32:12.683 --> 32:14.226
‐ ♪ When you were mine ♪

32:14.226 --> 32:16.728
♪ You said I was your everything ♪

32:16.728 --> 32:18.856
♪ What else did you find ♪

32:18.856 --> 32:22.067
♪ Tell me boy, what you're missing ♪

32:23.402 --> 32:25.070
[exhales]

32:25.070 --> 32:26.864
[phone ringing]

32:30.617 --> 32:33.745
ANNA [on voicemail]:
Hey! It's Anna. Leave a message.

32:33.745 --> 32:35.789
[voicemail beeps]
EDNA [on voicemail]: Hey, it's Edna.

32:35.789 --> 32:37.875
It's happening a lot faster
than I thought,

32:37.875 --> 32:40.752
and I want you by my side.
Call me, sis.

32:40.752 --> 32:42.504
[pounding on door]

32:43.505 --> 32:45.757
BAXTER:
This is it! Open it!

32:48.260 --> 32:49.011
[TV clicks off]

32:49.011 --> 32:50.429
[loud pounding on door]

32:50.429 --> 32:51.638
ANNA:
Fuck.

32:52.139 --> 32:54.975
What?
‐ Fuckin' rent! That's what.

32:54.975 --> 32:56.560
‐ I paid you.

32:57.102 --> 32:58.645
That increase happened after‐‐

32:58.645 --> 33:00.689
‐ The increase happened
when I say it did.

33:00.689 --> 33:02.983
It's 500 bucks. Now.

33:02.983 --> 33:06.195
‐ What are you gonna do?
Just drag me into
the middle of the street?

33:06.195 --> 33:07.529
[laughs]
[distant knocking]

33:07.529 --> 33:08.780
TENANT: Mr. Tannen!

33:08.780 --> 33:10.282
‐ Cops will do that for me.

33:10.282 --> 33:11.825
TENANT: Mr. Tannen!

33:11.825 --> 33:14.244
My toilet's overflowing!

33:16.705 --> 33:18.498
[distant siren blaring]

33:18.498 --> 33:21.001
♪ tense music playing ♪

33:21.001 --> 33:25.005
♪

33:42.731 --> 33:43.941
[light clicks]

33:52.824 --> 33:55.202
[eerie whispering]

34:15.430 --> 34:19.518
ANNA: "First there was only
the wild beasts and the red man.

34:19.518 --> 34:22.187
Then the white man came
and brought our people."

34:23.856 --> 34:25.899
"The Moss Haired Girl."

34:28.610 --> 34:31.238
"The house negress was a plain woman

34:31.238 --> 34:34.867
"who took up walking in them woods
when her work was done.

34:36.743 --> 34:40.080
"She'd see tress covered
in black moss so fine

34:40.080 --> 34:41.748
"it looked like massa hair.

34:41.748 --> 34:45.335
She stole the moss from the tree,
and made herself a wig."

34:56.430 --> 34:59.975
♪

35:00.684 --> 35:02.060
[doors thud open]

35:03.395 --> 35:04.563
[thudding]

35:05.063 --> 35:07.191
[voices whispering, overlapping]

35:16.366 --> 35:17.743
[thudding]

35:21.622 --> 35:24.041
[indistinct chatter]

35:35.260 --> 35:37.429
SHOW HOST [on TV]:
Welcome back to RMV.

35:37.429 --> 35:39.306
Can you believe it?
We are gonna do something so crazy

35:39.306 --> 35:40.891
and so different for us right now.

35:40.891 --> 35:42.851
Okay, the princess of soul, Sandra...

35:42.851 --> 35:46.063
‐ Ow! Ow.
‐ is now the queen of pop!

35:46.063 --> 35:48.690
Her newest single "I Get It"
is rising the pop charts,

35:48.690 --> 35:51.109
so let's give it up for her RMV debut.

35:51.109 --> 35:53.153
Here's Sandra!
[elevator dings]

35:53.570 --> 35:54.988
[elevator dings]

36:02.704 --> 36:04.331
[indistinct chatter]

36:04.915 --> 36:06.124
MAN: Yeah, man.

36:06.124 --> 36:07.501
MAN 2: Oh, who dat?

36:07.501 --> 36:09.086
‐ Oh, oh, my, my, my.

36:09.086 --> 36:11.672
Anna, uh, so I got these
Janet Jackson tickets, if you‐‐

36:12.714 --> 36:13.966
Feel like...

36:15.342 --> 36:17.135
ANNA: Hey, girl.
‐ Hi.

36:20.514 --> 36:22.099
ZORA: Hmm. Humph!

36:31.483 --> 36:32.776
[phone rings]

36:33.652 --> 36:35.195
[exhales]

36:37.573 --> 36:39.241
[winces]

36:39.241 --> 36:40.617
‐ Aah.

36:43.036 --> 36:45.080
Mm. [squeals]
ROSALYN: Wow.

36:45.747 --> 36:47.583
You look good, girl.

36:47.583 --> 36:49.877
‐ [laughs] Hey.

36:50.752 --> 36:52.087
Thanks to you.

36:53.839 --> 36:56.091
‐ I overheard Zora's hair speech.

36:56.091 --> 36:58.969
So, I thought she might like this.

36:58.969 --> 37:00.470
How does it feel?

37:00.929 --> 37:02.014
‐ It's fine.

37:02.014 --> 37:04.474
‐ I know. When I first got mine in,
I wasn't used to all that length.

37:04.474 --> 37:06.685
I was always swiping at my neck,

37:06.685 --> 37:09.188
like, "What is this?
‐ Yeah.

37:09.897 --> 37:13.275
‐ Oh, there's a planning meeting
in the conference room at 11:00,

37:13.275 --> 37:14.985
and Zora wants you there.

37:14.985 --> 37:17.196
‐ She... She does?

37:17.487 --> 37:18.697
‐ She does.

37:18.697 --> 37:20.282
[Anna laughs]

37:30.792 --> 37:32.002
ANNA: Ew!

37:32.002 --> 37:33.587
